	<dita:topic xmlns="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="UK14_Precedents_refpt">
  <title>refpt <lnpid>id-UK14-30223</lnpid></title>
  <body>
    <p><sourcexml>refpt</sourcexml> becomes <targetxml>ref:anchor</targetxml> with attributes as
      follows: <ul>
        <li><sourcexml>@id</sourcexml> becomes <targetxml>@id</targetxml></li>
        <li><sourcexml>@type</sourcexml> becomes <targetxml>@anchortype</targetxml> with value
            <sourcexml>"ext"</sourcexml> mapped to <targetxml>"global"</targetxml> and
            <sourcexml>"local"</sourcexml> mapped to <targetxml>"local"</targetxml>.</li>
      </ul></p>
    <p><b>Move Element:</b> When <sourcexml>refpt</sourcexml> is a child of
        <sourcexml>heading</sourcexml> or <sourcexml>heading/title</sourcexml> then move target
        <targetxml>ref:anchor</targetxml> to become a preceding sibling of
        <targetxml>heading</targetxml>.</p>
    <note><ul>
        <li><targetxml>ref:anchor/@id</targetxml> must conform to XML:ID standards as explained in
          the Introduction; including prepending underscore if value begins with number and
          replacing colon with underscore.</li>
        <li>The instruction on moving the element is particular to form markup. Otherwise these are
          usual rules for mapping to ref:anchor.</li>
      </ul></note>
    <pre>
        <b>EXAMPLE</b>
            
<b><i>Source XML</i></b>

&lt;COMMENTARYDOC&gt;
  &lt;comm:body&gt;
    &lt;level leveltype="precedent"&gt;
      &lt;bodytext&gt;
        &lt;form&gt;
          &lt;heading&gt;
            &lt;title&gt;&lt;refpt id="8OKE_1_140396:HT-CITATION" type="ext"/&gt;Fee letter&lt;/title&gt;
          &lt;/heading&gt;
          ...
        &lt;/form&gt;
      &lt;/bodytext&gt;
    &lt;/level&gt;
  &lt;/comm:body&gt;
&lt;/COMMENTARYDOC&gt;
 
<b><i>Target XML</i></b>

&lt;seclaw:seclaw&gt;
  &lt;seclaw:body&gt;
    &lt;form:form&gt;
      &lt;ref:anchor id="_8OKE_1_140396_HT-CITATION" type="global"/&gt;
      &lt;heading&gt;
        &lt;title&gt;Fee letter&lt;/title&gt;
      &lt;/heading&gt;
      &lt;form:info&gt;
        &lt;classify:classification&gt;
          &lt;classify:classitem&gt;
            &lt;classify:classitem-identifier&gt;
              &lt;classify:classcode normval="precedent"/&gt;
            &lt;/classify:classitem-identifier&gt;
          &lt;/classify:classitem&gt;
        &lt;/classify:classification&gt;
      &lt;/form:info&gt;
      ...
    &lt;/form:form&gt;
  &lt;/seclaw:body&gt;
&lt;/seclaw:seclaw&gt;

                </pre>
    <section>
      <title>Changes</title>
      <p>2016-03-27: <ph id="change_20160327_jm">Revised to broaden rule for moving
            <sourcexml>refpt</sourcexml>. Formerly covered only within
            <sourcexml>form/heading/title</sourcexml>. Now covers any occurrence within
            <sourcexml>heading</sourcexml> or <sourcexml>title</sourcexml>.</ph></p>
    </section>
  </body>
